            <fr:title text="Universal closure w.r.t variables">Universal closure w.r.t variables</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  If a formula <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> has a set of free variables:
</html:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \texttt {FV}(C) = \{x_1, x_2, \ldots , x_n\}
]]></fr:tex>
            <html:p>
  Then we can denote the universal closure <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall ^*]]></fr:tex> as representing the universal quantification over all those free variables, i.e. <fr:link href="/notes/hetzlkloibhofer2025/" title="An abstract fixed-point theorem for Horn formula equations" uri="https://kaierikniermann.github.io/notes/hetzlkloibhofer2025/" display-uri="hetzlkloibhofer2025" type="local">(1)</fr:link>:
</html:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \forall ^* C \equiv  \forall  x_1, x_2, \ldots , x_n.\ C
]]></fr:tex>
          </fr:mainmatter>
